### Title
Font-Awesome spinner breaks blazor UI rendering with no error

### Functional impact
UI Rendering seems to be broken or exhibit weird behavior

### Minimal repro steps
```
@page "/"

<div class="container-fluid">
    @if (IsLoading)
    {
        <i class="fa fa-spinner"></i> <!--comment this out, or wrap it in a div and it works-->
        <img src="/spinner.png" />

        <span>Loading</span>
    }
    else
    {
        <span>Hello World</span>
    }
</div>

@functions {

    private bool IsLoading { get; set; }

    protected override async Task OnInitAsync()
    {
        IsLoading = true;
        await Task.Delay(2000);
        IsLoading = false;
    }
}
```

### Expected result
I expect it to say Loading with a Loading spinner for 2 seconds and then say Hello World

### Actual result
It says loading forever.

### Further technical details
If I wrap the `<i class="fa fa-spinner"></i>` in a div like this: `<div><i class="fa fa-spinner"></i></div>` or just omit it altogether, I get the expected result.

